Durban - Convicted killer Rajivee Soni's case was postponed to December 12. Soni's application for leave to appeal his conviction was due to be heard in the Durban High Court on Wednesday. The matter was adjourned as the judgement on his sentence was not available. Soni intends on applying for bail if his application for leave to appeal is granted. He is currently serving a 30-year prison sentence at the New Prison in Pietermaritzburg for the 2013 murder of doctor Bhavish Sewram. Soni was convicted on various - 25 years for murder; 5 years for defeating the course of justice; 18 months for assault and 5 years for conspiracy to commit murder. The judge ruled that the sentences would run concurrently and jailed Soni to an effective 30 years. The Pietermaritzburg father of two was gunned down outside his surgery in Raisethorpe. Soni masterminded the murder after he suspected that Sewram was involved in a relationship with his wife. He hired former policeman Brian Treasurer to carry out the hit and paid him R100 000. Treasurer died in prison while serving a life sentence. Hitmen Mfaniseni Nxumalo is also serving a life sentence. Daily News